body_html:
it's likely that the first time you ran the example, the cifar10 dataset was being downloaded.
And when you subsequently ran it with py3.5, it didn't have to redownload it.
If you switch back to py3.6, it should be fast.

body:
it's likely that the first time you ran the example, the cifar10 dataset was being downloaded.
And when you subsequently ran it with py3.5, it didn't have to redownload it.
If you switch back to py3.6, it should be fast.
